### 🚀 I. Model Management Commands (Working with Files)

These commands handle downloading, listing, and checking models before you 
can run them.

| Example Command | Purpose | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `lms list` | **List Models** | Shows all the LLMs that have been 
successfully downloaded or indexed by LM Studio on your machine. |
| `lms pull <model-name>` | **Download Model** | Downloads a specific 
model file (e.g., `gemma4:7b`). This is required before you can run it. |
| `lms delete <model-name>` | **Clean Up** | Removes a large, unneeded 
model file from your local storage to free up disk space. |
| `lms info <model-name>` | **Check Model Info** | Provides details about 
the model, such as required VRAM/RAM and quantization level. |

### 💻 II. Execution & Server Commands (The Core Function)

These commands start the actual operation of the LLM—either for a chat 
session or for connecting to external apps.

| Example Command | Purpose | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `lms run <model-name>` | **Direct Run/Chat** | Starts an immediate, 
interactive command-line session with the specified model. This is used if 
you just want to chat and don't need to integrate it into other apps. |
| `lms serve --model <model-name>` | **Start Local Server (Primary)** | 
Launches the core functionality: starting a local API server endpoint. 
Other programs can connect to this running service using 
`http://localhost:[port]`. **This is critical for development.** |
| `lms stop` | **Stop Service** | Gracefully shuts down any currently 
running model or API server managed by `lms`. |
| `lms serve --hot-reload` | **Develop/Debug Mode** | Starts the server in 
a mode that automatically detects and reloads changes to configuration or 
code, useful for developers. |

### 🔧 III. Configuration & Utility Commands (Settings)

These commands manage the environment, connections, and settings of your 
overall setup.

| Example Command | Purpose | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `lms config --port <number>` | **Set Port** | Allows you to specify 
which network port the local server should use (useful if another program 
is already using the default port). |
| `lms status` | **Check Status** | Reports the current state of the `lms` 
utility—e.g., Is the model loaded? Is the server running? What resources 
are being used? |
| `lms version` | **Check Version** | Confirms that the CLI is working and 
shows which specific commit/version you are running (as you demonstrated). 
|

